ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[See full article with references at the URL above.
Norovirus is the leading cause of gastroenteritis outbreaks worldwide. The most common norovirus strain (genogroup II genotype 4) is a major cause of these outbreaks. New norovirus strains emerge about every 2 to 4 years. Often, but not always, these new strains lead to an increase in outbreaks. This article reports a new norovirus strain, GII.P16-GII.2, associated with recent outbreaks in Germany as well as outbreaks elsewhere globally.

A map of Germany can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4797915,101 - Mod.LK]


